INSERT INTO questions (type, content, options, answer, explanation, difficulty, category, tags, year) VALUES ('single', '75. IPsec, also known as the internet Protocol (71), defines the architecture for security services for IP network traffic, [Psec describes the framework for providing security a the IP layer,as well as the suite of protocols designed to provide that security:through (72) and encryption of IP network packets. [Pec can be used protect network data, for example, by setting up circuits using IPsec (73) , in which all data being sent between two endpoints is encrypted, as with a Virtual (74) Network connection ;for encrypting application layer data ;and for providing security for routers sending routing data across the public internet. Internet traffic can also be secured from host to host without the use of 1Psec, for example by encryption at the (75) layer with HTTP Secure(TTPS) or an the transport layer wit the Transport Layer Security (TLS) protocol.', '["B. Secretary", "C. Secret", "D. Secondary", "B. authentication"]', '', '', 2, '2015年综合知识', '2015,综合知识', 2015);
